    "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. In Focus, go to Settings - Search - \"+ Add another search engine\".\r\n2. Add valid search engine credentials, but do not tap on \"Save\". The focus is on the last character from the URL field.\r\n3. Rotate the device to landscape and observe the focus of the bar.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nThe focus remains on the URL field, after the last inserted character.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nThe focus jumps on the \"Search engine name\" field in front of the inserted characters.\r\n\r\n### Device information\r\n* Android device: Sony Xperia Z5 Premium (Android 7.1.1), HTC 10 (Android 8)\r\n* Focus version: 8.15.2\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40694158/116222604-6a290a80-a757-11eb-8ff9-933d728730d6.mp4\r\n",
